      "id": "PopularPost259054",
      "post_content": "I don't see why so many people dislike this. Paying life for power is a good way of teaching new players what it means to be playing black. Furthermore, there's nothing wrong with +3/+1 on one of your creatures. Sure, its CMC:P/T ratio isn't as good as [Unholy Strength](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Unholy Strength)'s, but it still does pack more power in one single card.",
